title: Remove `<reference path="../xxx/xxx.d.ts">` from definitions files
body:
...and replace it with `import * as Xxx from "xxx"` or `<reference types="xxx"/>`

Besides that I have added `tsconfig.json` for all changed modules and fixed tests.

I also made the following changes:
### Changed to module style (need careful review)
- angular-websocket
- angular-xeditable
- angular-q-spread
- backbone-fetch-cache
- backlog-js
- file-type
- geojson2osm
- inversify-binding-decorators
- inversify-devtools
- inversify-restify-utils
- inversify-inject-decorators
- inversify-logger-middleware
- karma-chai-sinon
- koa-json-error
- libxslt
- react-daterange-picker
- reacti18next
- rx.wamp
- sinon-as-promised
- watchify
- whatwg-streams (required to fix whatwg-fetch)
### Quick fixes to get tests working
- d3kit: Added `|any` to `LayerOrganizer.create`'s `config` parameter
- dva: added `:any` to some parameters in tests
- multer: made sure `Express` is declared globally
- ngmap: For some reason I had to change "angular.IPromise" to "ng.IPromise"
- notify.js: Got rid of the namespace since we're extending jquery
- react-autosuggest: Used `React.HTMLAttributes<any>`, `React.FormEvent<any>`, and many parameters must be annotated as `any`
- react-data-grid: Used `React.SyntheticEvent<any>`
- react-file-input: Used `React.SyntheticEvent<any>`
- react-file-reader-input: Used `React.SyntheticEvent<any>`
- react-sortable-hoc: Used `MouseEvent<any>` and `TouchEvent<any>`
- react-swipeable: Used `React.TouchEvent<any>`
- react-textarea-autosize: Used `React.FormEvent<any>`
- react-user-tour: Used `HTMLAttributers<any>`, and changed a div's `class` to `classID` in tests
- victory: Used `React.DomAttributes<any>` and `React.SyntheticEvent<any>`
- whatwg-fetch: Used "HeadersInit" instead of "HeadersMap"

Waiting on #11284

title: Node.JS EventEmitter accepts symbols as event names
body:
case 2. Improvement to existing type definition.

[Event names are allowed to be symbols as well as strings](https://nodejs.org/api/events.html#events_emitter_on_eventname_listener), since [Node 5.6.0](https://github.com/nodejs/node/blob/master/doc/changelogs/CHANGELOG_V5.md#2016-02-09-version-560-stable-jasnell).

I haven't applied it to `node-4.d.ts` as it was only introduced in [Node 4.4.0](https://nodejs.org/en/blog/release/v4.4.0/).

The change to `EventEmitter#eventNames()` type is a breaking change to the definition as it now returns a looser set of types, but the API has been like that since 5.6.0, so I don't know what your policy is on this.
